ssh -i karanss02.pem ubuntu@ipaddress (public ipv4 address from aws)

sudo apt-get update   (to update the system whenever you connect to instance for 1st time)

local:-
how to transfer any file from local system to instance
(scp -i karanss02.pem (file_name which we want to transfer) ubuntu@ipaddress:/location_of_folder in instance where we want to transfer file)
scp -i karanss02.pem dummy.txt ubuntu@ipaddress

to_change_ownership of particular folder
sudo chown username_of_owner:username_of_owner foldername

sudo mkdir folder_name   -> To create directory

ls -l  -> for permission

ctrlx -> to close the command (e.g nano)

sudo apt-get install name_of_file  (to install any library)

nano dummypython.py
